<p>
  Code snippet can be a block of code, and
  {% include '@bolt-components-code-snippet/code-snippet.twig' with {
    display: 'inline',
    content: 'display'
  } only %}
  is set to
  {% include '@bolt-components-code-snippet/code-snippet.twig' with {
    display: 'inline',
    content: 'block'
  } only %}
  by default.
</p>

{% set blockSnippet %}
display: block;
margin: 0 0 1.65rem 0;
{% endset %}

{% embed '@bolt-components-code-snippet/code-snippet.twig' with {
  display: 'block',
  lang: 'scss',
  content: blockSnippet
} only %}
{% endembed %}

<p>
  Well, code snippet can also be inline like this
  {% include '@bolt-components-code-snippet/code-snippet.twig' with {
    display: 'inline',
    lang: 'scss',
    content: 'display:inline;'
  } only %}
  when you set
  {% include '@bolt-components-code-snippet/code-snippet.twig' with {
    display: 'inline',
    content: 'display'
  } only %}
  to be
  {% include '@bolt-components-code-snippet/code-snippet.twig' with {
    display: 'inline',
    content: 'inline'
  } only %}
  instead.
</p>
